  "text": "After Crossover Figure 3 . GA crossover operation. [CITATION_1] . Mutation: The process of alternating or switching between certain genes within one chromosome to obtain other chromosomes as new input solutions for the next generation. Mutation aims to reach the best likely solutions in order to reach a high positive level of diversity to the population; also, it helps not to release in the local optimum [CITATION_2] . There are several methods of mutations; starts with bit conversion mutation type and evolves to other types that fit several locations, see Figure 4 .",
